<a name="5268"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">International Exhibitors: Secure Your Travel Visas</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/photos/plane.jpg" width=125 height=84>If you are an exhibitor that requires a visa to enter the U.S., request your letter of invitation and make your appointment for a visa interview early. Wait times for a visa interview can be several weeks or more in many countries, especially during peak travel periods. We strongly urge you to register for CES when exhibitor registration opens on July 25 and request a letter of invitation as soon as possible. For helpful tips on securing your visa, visit <A href="http://www.CESweb.org/International">www.CESweb.org/International</A>.<BR><BR>Also, a recent policy change requires all visitors to the U.S. from visa-waiver countries to register online and be authorized for entry as part of the new Electronic System for Travel Authorization program. <A href="https://esta.cbp.dhs.gov/esta/esta.html?_flowExecutionKey=_cDDA61A31-654F-6D58-BAC3-66311FBF2145_kBE0B84A0-8F01-1354-C6D3-2F137B8661DE" target=_blank>Learn more about this program</A>.<BR><br />
