<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/IndustryForum_logo.jpg" width=250 height=56>Registration for the <A href="http://www.ce.org/events/default.asp?siteUrl=http://speaker.ce.org/index.cfm?do=cus.meeting|meetingID=1460" target=_blank>2011 CEA Industry Forum</A> is open! Take advantage of early-bird rates and save up to $175 by <A href="http://www.ce.org/events/default.asp?siteUrl=http://speaker.ce.org/index.cfm?do=cus.meeting|meetingID=1460" target=_blank>registering now</A>. The CEA Industry Forum is a crucial networking and educational event for CE industry professionals. This must-attend event provides the right mix of industry attendees and educational sessions to help you grow your business and remain competitive in the CE industry. <BR><BR>The conference takes place October 23-26 at the <A href="https://resweb.passkey.com/Resweb.do?mode=welcome_ei_new&eventID=3420143" target=_blank>Manchester Grand Hyatt</A> in San Diego, Calif., and includes events such as the CE Hall of Fame dinner, a new health and fitness track and much more. View the <A href="http://www.ce.org/industryforum" target=_blank>full conference schedule</A> and check back often for updates. Buy one registration [insert link] at full price and bring your colleagues for 20 percent off. <BR><BR>Make sure to <A href="https://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=181069545281283" target=_blank>RSVP on Facebook</A> to let everyone know you’re coming!
