    <p><strong>Expand Your Show Presence</strong><br> 
by Susan Littleton</p>
    <p>It may be difficult to believe, but we are already halfway through 2011 and only six months from the 2012 International CES, the industry’s largest trade-only event.<BR>By now, your company’s preparations for the 2012 show are well underway. Booth space is confirmed. Hotel rooms and airfare are being booked. You may have even started to schedule meetings with clients, partners and the press. As you continue to prepare for CES, it is important to consider your entire show participation, not just exhibit space. Besides securing the best possible booth, have you explored <A href="/exhibitors/sponsorships/default.asp">additional ways</A> to enhance your organization’s presence at the show?<BR><BR><A href="/exhibitors/sponsorships/sponsorships.asp">Sponsorship opportunities</A> at CES can help your company achieve a more targeted and impactful presence. Our traditional inventory includes everything from broad-exposure items like banners, email stations, badge lanyards and show bags, to more specific, targeted marketing like division reception sponsorships and our VIP buyer program. Onsite advertising is a great way to get your brand in front of the more than 140,000 attendees expected at the show.
&nbsp;
Promotional opportunities also include <A href="/exhibitors/sponsorships/pressOpportunitites.asp">targeted press outreach</A> such as CES Unveiled@NY and CES Unveiled in Las Vegas. The official CES press events attract over 300 media and analysts in New York and more than 800 at the Las Vegas event and is the best way to receive press attention and build buzz before the show. Other opportunities include sponsorships of press and analyst breakfast or lunch, the Online Media Center, media gifts and notepads.
&nbsp;
Advertising is also another great way to get exposure before and during the show.&nbsp;CES offers <A href="/exhibitors/sponsorships/printAdvertising.asp">advertising opportunities</A> in the Official CES Directory and CES Daily print publications as well as in the Preshow Planner and Show Guide. And speaking of the directory, you can also customize and enhance your online directory listing through a bevy of <A href="/exhibitors/sponsorships/default.asp">package options</A> through our vendor Map Your Show.<BR><BR>Most companies focus on their booth as the core of show participation, but our most successful exhibitors pursue a more integrated approach – one that leverages a multi-faceted approach to marketing. And while our traditional inventory of promotions and sponsorships is limited based on renewals, we also encourage you to bring us your own ideas. If there is an attendee segment you'd like to reach, a technology you'd like to promote, or a new product or partnership you'd like to publicize, we would love to discuss ways to develop a customized sponsorship opportunity for your organization.
&nbsp;
If you’re interested in learning more information about all these opportunities, please contact Liz Tardif at <A href="mailto:ltardif@CE.org">ltardif@CE.org</A>.<BR><BR>Sincerely,<BR><IMG src="/images/content/Susan_Littleton_sig.jpg"><BR><BR>Susan Littleton<BR>
